message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Multipath QUIC Performance and Energy Evaluation in Controlled IPv6 Testbed
abstract: The dataset documents a systematic evaluation of multipath QUIC transport
  under varied congestion‑control algorithms and scheduler policies. Experiments were
  conducted on three nodes configured with dual‑path IPv6 connectivity, traffic shaping,
  and controlled latency to emulate fast‑ and slow‑path conditions. For each configuration,
  ten runs recorded throughput, energy consumption, and QLOG traces, enabling quantitative
  comparison of protocol performance across network profiles. The results include
  raw measurement logs, visualization outputs, and aggregated plots illustrating key
  metrics.
